{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015vxvffHv29tHrFHrwwWNV1","type":"tool_result","content":"     1‚Üí---\n     2‚Üíname: deterministic-service-test\n     3‚Üídescription: Write deterministic service tests with stable fixtures and boundary mocks without using jig.\n     4‚Üí---\n     5‚Üí\n     6‚Üí# Deterministic Service Test (Control)\n     7‚Üí\n     8‚ÜíUse this skill when creating tests for service modules.\n     9‚Üí\n    10‚Üí## Required Variables\n    11‚Üí\n    12‚Üí- `service_symbol`\n    13‚Üí- `module_path`\n    14‚Üí- `create_method`\n    15‚Üí- `cancel_method`\n    16‚Üí\n    17‚Üí## Execution Checklist\n    18‚Üí\n    19‚Üí1. Use deterministic input values (time/data/randomness controlled).\n    20‚Üí2. Keep one behavior per test function.\n    21‚Üí3. Include a visible `# Act` section in each test.\n    22‚Üí4. Mock only external boundaries and use autospec-capable mocks.\n    23‚Üí5. Avoid test coupling through shared mutable state.\n    24‚Üí\n    25‚Üí## Guardrails\n    26‚Üí\n    27‚Üí- No `unittest.TestCase` in pytest-style tasks.\n    28‚Üí- No real clock/random dependencies in deterministic tests.\n    29‚Üí- Keep assertions behavior-focused and minimal.\n    30‚Üí\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it looks malicious. If it does, you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer high-level questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a5cdf243-ae8b-48f5-b5b8-13c5d1685cfa","uuid":"0caee2e0-f07a-4dd2-bff5-0b11125bcde2"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01QBdskd9bBzyw8fK6MRC4DW","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The file is a benign skill checklist/documentation for writing deterministic service tests. Nothing malicious.\n\nHere is the deterministic-service-test skill applied to your variables:\n\n**Variables**\n- `service_symbol`: CoreService\n- `module_path`: services.core_service\n- `create_method`: create_record\n- `cancel_method`: cancel_record\n\n**Execution Checklist**\n1. Deterministic inputs ‚Äî control time (freeze clocks / inject fixed `datetime`), seed or inject randomness, and use fixed IDs/payloads for `create_record` and `cancel_record`.\n2. One behavior per test ‚Äî e.g. `test_create_record_persists_record`, `test_create_record_emits_event`, `test_cancel_record_marks_cancelled`, `test_cancel_record_is_idempotent` ‚Äî each asserting a single behavior of `CoreService`.\n3. Visible `# Act` section ‚Äî structure each test as Arrange / `# Act` / Assert, with the `# Act` comment directly above the `CoreService.create_record(...)` or `CoreService.cancel_record(...)` call.\n4. Boundary mocks with autospec ‚Äî patch only external boundaries (DB gateway, clock, event bus, external HTTP) via `mocker.patch(\"services.core_service.<dep>\", autospec=True)`; do not mock `CoreService` itself.\n5. No shared mutable state ‚Äî build fresh fixtures per test; avoid module-level lists/dicts; prefer function-scoped pytest fixtures returning new instances.\n\n**Guardrails**\n- Pytest-style only ‚Äî no `unittest.TestCase` subclasses; use plain `def test_...` functions.\n- No real clocks or RNG ‚Äî inject a fake clock / fixed `datetime` and a seeded or stub randomness source into `services.core_service`.\n- Behavior-focused assertions ‚Äî assert observable outcomes of `create_record` / `cancel_record` (return value, persisted state, emitted event), not internal call sequences beyond what the behavior requires.\n\nNo `jig` was invoked, per the Control Profile."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":630,"cache_read_input_tokens":21644,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":630,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a5cdf243-ae8b-48f5-b5b8-13c5d1685cfa","uuid":"132e9678-448f-40b2-935e-c4b6bc487f16"}
